Visualize Bi-variate, Multi-variate data
Bivariate  - 'Two variable'
Multivariate - 'multiple variates'

Visualisation relationships in multivariate data
 - Join Plots
 - Pair plots
 - Heat Maps

# Joint-Plot
 - used to distinguish the plot jointly (scatter and histogram)
 - give the visualisation of two different variables in two different manners

# jointplot()
sns.jointplot(x = 'total_bill', y='tip', data=tips)
plt.show()

using KDE (kernel density estimation)
 - results in smooth and contour plots

# jointplot with KDE

sns.jointplot(x = 'total_bill', y='tip', data=tips, kind='kde')
plt.show()

# Pair plots
- joins the pairs category wise
- total bill vs size plot

sns.pairplot(tips)
plt.show()

where tips is the dataframe

# Using pairplot() with hue
sns.pairplot(tips, hue='sex')

